{"lemma":"فارِس","slug":"فارِس","root":"ف.ر.س","root_slug":"ف-ر-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33513"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%B3"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"horseman, rider"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"knight, cavalier (warrior, especially of the Middle Ages)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chevalier"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hero"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cavalry","tags":["in-plural"]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Persia"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Middle Persian 𐭯𐭠𐭫𐭮𐭩 (pʾlsy /⁠pārs⁠/), from Old Persian 𐎱𐎠𐎼𐎿 (p-a-r-s /⁠pārsa⁠/)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33513","headword_ar":"فَارِسٌ","root":"frs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasa","text_ar":"فَرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaArisu","text_ar":"الفَارِسُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so called because he breaks the neck of his prey;] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfaruwsu","text_ar":"الفَرُوسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which has an intensive signification,] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfar~aAsu","text_ar":"الفَرَّاسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) which last [also] has an intensive signification, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw firaAsK","text_ar":"اَبُو فِرَاسٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw far~aAsK","text_ar":"اَبُو فَرَّاسٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almufotarisu","text_ar":"المُفْتَرِسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfironaAsu","text_ar":"الفِرْنَاسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfironawosu","text_ar":"الفِرْنَوْسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", a word of a measure not mentioned by Sb, (IJ, M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuraAnisu","text_ar":"الفُرَانِسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfironaAsu","text_ar":"الفِرْنَاسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is said by IKh to be applied to the lion because he is the chief of the beasts of prey, signifies, (O,) or signifies also, (S,) used as an epithet applied to the lion, (S, * M, * O,) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuraAnisu","text_ar":"الفُرَانِسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * M, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thick-necked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is wont to break the neck of his prey;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the former of these two,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rapacious"},{"kind":"text","text":"lion; (O;) and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"in these words is augmentative: (Sb, S, M, O:) and you also say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEN far~aAsN","text_ar":"سَبْعٌ فَرَّاسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asadN far~aAsN","text_ar":"اَسَدٌ فَرَّاسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rapacious beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that often seizes others and breaks their necks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"master,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"owner, of a horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;) a possessive epithet; (M;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAbinN","text_ar":"لَابِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAmirN","text_ar":"تَامِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a horseman; a rider upon a horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, Mgh, O, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon a mule;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, A, Mgh, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon an ass:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, Mgh, Msb:) or a rider upon a mule is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisN EalaY","text_ar":"فَارِسٌ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagolK","text_ar":"بَغْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (ISk, S, O, Msb, K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisu bagolK","text_ar":"فَارِسُ بَغْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, O;) and a rider upon an ass,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisN EalaY HimaArK","text_ar":"فَارِسٌ عَلَى حِمَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (ISk, S, Mgh, O, Msb;) and a rider upon any solid-hoofed beast,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisN EalaY *iY HaAfirK","text_ar":"فَارِسٌ عَلَى ذِى حَافِرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or these phrases are not used: (K:) 'Omárah Ibn- 'Akeel Ibn-Bilál Ibn-Jereer says, (S,) or AZ, (Msb,) I do not call the owner of the mule, nor the owner of the ass,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisN","text_ar":"فَارِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but I call them"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bag~aAlN","text_ar":"بَغَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ham~aArN","text_ar":"حَمَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, Msb:) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisN","text_ar":"فَارِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is often best rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cavalier:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furosaAnN","text_ar":"فُرْسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaArisu","text_ar":"فَوَارِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which latter is [more usual, but] anomalous, (S, M, O, Msb, K,) for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaAEilu","text_ar":"فَوَاعِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [regularly] the measure of the pl. of a sing. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilapN","text_ar":"فَاعِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DawaAribu","text_ar":"ضَوَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAribapN","text_ar":"ضَارِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or of an epithet of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilN","text_ar":"فَاعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applying to a female, as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAy^iDu","text_ar":"حَوَايِضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAy^iDN","text_ar":"حَايِضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or of a sing. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilN","text_ar":"فَاعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applying to a thing that is not a human being or not a rational being, as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawaAzilu","text_ar":"بَوَازِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAzilN","text_ar":"بَازِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAy^iTN","text_ar":"حَوَايِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAy^iTN","text_ar":"حَايِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and there are no instances like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaArisu","text_ar":"فَوَارِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"except those of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hawaAliku","text_ar":"هَوَالِكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawaAkisu","text_ar":"نَوَاكِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xawaAlifu","text_ar":"خَوَالِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and some other words enumerated in the Msb and TA]; (S, Msb;) and as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwArs","text_ar":"فوارس"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not applied to females, no ambiguity is feared from its usage: (S, O:) [ISd says,] we have not heard"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN faArisapN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ فَارِسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b2-  Also, (As,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisN EalaY Alxayoli","text_ar":"فَارِسٌ عَلَى الخَيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skilful in horsemanship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the management of horses."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, * S.) ―         -b3-  And hence, the former, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fArs","text_ar":"فارس"},{"kind":"text","text":",) (assumed tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skilful in anything that he endeavours to do."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfawaArisu","text_ar":"الفَوَارِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Four stars of the constellation Cygnus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw. See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dajaAjN","text_ar":"دَجَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisu Aln~aZari","text_ar":"فَارِسُ النَّظَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binaZarihi","text_ar":"بِنَظَرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEayonihi","text_ar":"بِعَيْنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who acts deliberately, and examines:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, and so in Hr p. 356:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who possesses"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firaAsap","text_ar":"فِرَاسَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intuitive perception,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowing by means of examination."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisN fiY Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"فَارِسٌ فِى النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seeing into the internal, inward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intrinsic, states,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of men"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisu","text_ar":"فَارِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Mgh, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisN","text_ar":"فَارِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in some copies of the K,) [the former if fem., as it is a proper name, the latter if masc.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain nation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) [namely, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persians;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfurosu","text_ar":"الفُرْسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) generally fem.: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furosN","text_ar":"فُرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisiY~N","text_ar":"فَارِسِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a rel. n. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisu","text_ar":"فَارِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense next following: (M:) [or, rather,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furosN","text_ar":"فُرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a coll. gen. n., and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArisiY~N","text_ar":"فَارِسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is its n. un.] ―         -b2-  Also, (S, O, but in the K “ or ”)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The country of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furos","text_ar":"فُرْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, K;) [i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persia;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a country of a certain nation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2369}],"source_refs":["O","K","TA","S","A","M","IJ","Sb","ISk","Mgh","Msb","As"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B3/","headword_ar":"فارس","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_27","lexicon_en":"Al-Barakatī, al-Taʿrīfāt al-Fiqhīya (d. 1975 CE)","lexicon_ar":"التعريفات الفقهيّة للبركتي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=48114#6febdc","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">فارس</span><span>ُ: جِيلٌ من الناس وبلادهم.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_48","lexicon_en":"Sultan Qaboos Encyclopedia of Arab Names (Sultan Qaboos University, 1985)","lexicon_ar":"موسوعة السلطان قابوس لأسماء العرب","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=48114#0fe3f9","body_html":"فارس<br>عن اللغة اللاتينية بمعنى ملئ بالشباب والحيوية."}]}}